entries.meaning: (statistics) The value of a distribution for which some fraction of the sample lies below.
examples: The q-quantile is the same as the (1/q)-fractile.

adjectives.description: fractile (comparative more fractile, superlative most fractile)

entries.meaning: Describing the quality of a sedimentary stone as it relates to the sediments to cohesively bond without fracturing.
examples: A stone with a low fractile strength lacks tensile strength and will crack or crumble under stress or pressure.
